fields.physical_description: A hardback sketchbook used by Julie Verhoeven as a scrapbook and sketchbook. The front outer cover has 4 images on it of varying sizes and is covered over completely in cellotape, the back cover has a full length image of a female figure cut from a magazine, also completely cellotaped over. The pages within are covered primarily in cut-out images from magazines as well as post cards and Verhoeven's own sketches and hand written notes.
fields.dimensions: height: 307 mm spine, width: 208 mm hardback cover, depth: 30 mm spine
fields.materials_techniques: Collaged items as well as pencil drawings.
